value.0: Layered in fine leather and furs, Alf is no doubt one of the warmest people in Howness. He seems to make a good living off of his job too, and he knows it. Every now and then the man gives his moustache a twirl.
Everything about this man is odd, even the way he dresses. One can only guess why he was named Odd. You would think he would get cold.
A middle aged man dressed in Helmite clergy robes.
Hrolf is more silent than not these days. He wears an angry frown most of the time and only his wife is treated with quiet kindness.
Grieving for the loss of her son, Gundrunn keeps conversations short, but polite, and mostly sticks close to her husband.
A pretty young woman, Unnr seems more interested in what the tailors have to offer rather than anything else.
A finely dressed man. For Howness, at least.

The Arctic Dwarf Olaf is a long time member of the Howness community. How he came to the town and why remains a mystery to most people. Some have assumed he's an exile of the Great Glacier. Whatever his history, he diligently creates arms and armor. While not the best smith around Olaf accepts help from Grimli the Dwarf who can usually be found inside the Temple of Helm. The two working together makes up the difference and between them quite the selection of wares is sold. To show how strong his loyalty to the people of Howness truly is, Olaf even goes as far as putting up with his new resident; a crazy gnome inventor refugee from the Gnomish Testing Range.
A handsome man who diligently watches over his shop and workers.

value.0: Susanne Larssdottir is an aged, stern looking woman. Poor of sight, she is often found squinting heavily at those she talks to and she bears the sigil of a wolverine proudly.

Pjeter Snorrison is a much more friendly counterpart to the other two Elders of Howness. Often found giving a treat or two to the children, or telling wild tales of his days wrestling the wildlife into submission. True tales or not, he has clearly seen his own fair amount of action from the scars that riddle his body. He bears one ring on each hand, both with the marking of a bear upon them.

Hinrik Kiallakson is a rather dapper dressed man with an impressive beard, golden rings tying off the three smaller sections. Looking rather muscular despite his age, a rather nasty looking scar replaces his left eye. Around his neck he carries an iron wrought necklac with the stamp of an anvil engraved into it.
